      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, powered by the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This specimen exhibits exceptional mechanical integrity, featuring factory-spec compression across all rotor faces and a perfectly synchronized sequential boost transition. The lightweight front-midship chassis retains its original double-wishbone aluminum suspension geometry and Torsen limited-slip differential, delivering surgical handling precision. Meticulously maintained with a focus on thermal management, the cooling system and vacuum routing remain in pristine, OEM configuration. The exterior finish is flawless, complemented by an interior that shows no signs of sun degradation or bolster wear, representing a rare, unmolested survivor of Japanese performance engineering.",
